docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:8: trailing whitespace.
+- **Implementation status:** local executable kernel
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:30: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:31: trailing whitespace.
+## P0 claim
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:32: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:33: trailing whitespace.
+Given a declarative mission and a local seed project, PROMETHEUS can create three or more deterministic candidate implementations in isolated Git worktrees, run real commands against each, rank viable candidates, adversarially challenge the leader, apply a declared repair when the challenge exposes a failure, promote one passing result, and emit a hash-verifiable receipt and capability genome.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:34: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:35: trailing whitespace.
+## Verified when
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:36: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:37: trailing whitespace.
+P0 is complete only when all of the following are observed in a clean environment:
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:38: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:39: trailing whitespace.
+1. Kernel tests pass.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:40: trailing whitespace.
+2. Three candidate worktrees are created from one captured seed commit.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:41: trailing whitespace.
+3. Candidate edits are distinct and committed.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:42: trailing whitespace.
+4. Standard tests execute for every candidate.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:43: trailing whitespace.
+5. Exactly one leader is challenged.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:44: trailing whitespace.
+6. The bootstrap leader fails the adversarial gate.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:45: trailing whitespace.
+7. A repair commit is applied.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:46: trailing whitespace.
+8. Standard and adversarial tests pass after repair.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:47: trailing whitespace.
+9. Exactly one workspace is promoted.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:48: trailing whitespace.
+10. Receipt verification succeeds.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:49: trailing whitespace.
+11. A capability genome references the receipt hash.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:50: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:51: trailing whitespace.
+## Explicit non-claims
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:52: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:53: trailing whitespace.
+P0 does not claim autonomous model reasoning, arbitrary code synthesis, production sandboxing, multi-agent concurrency, EDEN/Cali connectivity, Thoth persistence, or ProofGrid network publication. ServerForge planning and live API mutation are implemented, but no live Discord deployment is claimed until an authorized guild passes preflight, apply, and verify with retained evidence.
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:54: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:55: trailing whitespace.
+## Promotion sequence
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:56: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:57: trailing whitespace.
+- **P0A — Ignition:** deterministic local mission-to-proof kernel
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:58: trailing whitespace.
+- **P0B — Direct bridge:** ServerForge topology, preflight, snapshot, apply, and verify available from startup
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:59: trailing whitespace.
+- **P1 — External proof:** execute the bridge against the new authorized Discord server and capture the case study
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:60: trailing whitespace.
+- **P2 — Recursive build:** PROMETHEUS applies the loop to its own repository
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:61: trailing whitespace.
+- **P3 — Estate bridges:** EDEN/Cali execution, Thoth memory, ProofGrid evidence, ServerForge Observatory
docs/BUILD_TRUTH.md:62: trailing whitespace.
+- **P4 — Product hardening:** installation, threat model, observability, recovery, release artifacts, competition demo
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:1: trailing whitespace.
+# Competition Demo
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:2: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:3: trailing whitespace.
+## Core claim
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:4: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:5: trailing whitespace.
+PROMETHEUS does not merely generate an answer. It creates competing implementations, makes the winner survive an independent attack, repairs what breaks, and exposes the entire promotion lineage through a live Discord nervous system.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:6: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:7: trailing whitespace.
+## Seven-minute proof sequence
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:8: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:9: trailing whitespace.
+1. **Mission (45s):** show frozen mission, three strategies, acceptance gates, and execution policy.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:10: trailing whitespace.
+2. **Forge (60s):** create three real Git worktrees and show distinct commits.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:11: trailing whitespace.
+3. **Standard gate (45s):** all viable candidates run the same tests; deterministic scoring selects the lowest-cost leader.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:12: trailing whitespace.
+4. **Adversarial reversal (60s):** the apparently best leader fails boolean/NaN boundary attacks.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:13: trailing whitespace.
+5. **Repair (45s):** apply a visible repair commit and rerun both gates.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:14: trailing whitespace.
+6. **Promotion proof (60s):** verify receipt hash, event-chain history `[fail, pass]`, artifact hashes, and capability genome.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:15: trailing whitespace.
+7. **ServerForge (90s):** run the same startup into the new Discord server; show mission control, adversarial findings, ProofGrid, telemetry, and before/after verification.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:16: trailing whitespace.
+8. **Close (30s):** reproduce on a clean runner and display the GitHub Actions proof artifact.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:17: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:18: trailing whitespace.
+## Judge-facing differentiators
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:19: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:20: trailing whitespace.
+- Counterfactual candidates are isolated code lineages, not three paragraphs in one model response.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:21: trailing whitespace.
+- The leader can lose after selection; the adversarial gate has real authority.
docs/COMPETITION_DEMO.md:22: trailing whitespace.
