+# ServerForge: New-Server Bootstrap
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:2: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:3: trailing whitespace.
+ServerForge is connected from the first startup, but Discord retains one human trust boundary: a server owner creates the empty server and approves the application installation. Bots are added to servers through Discord’s OAuth2 bot authorization flow; once installed with the required permissions, the documented guild, role, and channel endpoints support the live build.
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:4: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:5: trailing whitespace.
+## One-time trust handoff
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:6: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:7: trailing whitespace.
+1. Create a new empty Discord server named `PROMETHEUS Forge — Live Case Study`.
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:8: trailing whitespace.
+2. Create or select the Discord application and bot in the Developer Portal.
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:9: trailing whitespace.
+3. Record the application ID and the new server’s guild ID.
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:10: trailing whitespace.
+4. Generate the pinned install URL:
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:11: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:12: trailing whitespace.
+   ```powershell
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:13: trailing whitespace.
+   $env:DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID = "YOUR_APPLICATION_ID"
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:14: trailing whitespace.
+   $env:DISCORD_GUILD_ID = "YOUR_NEW_SERVER_ID"
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:15: trailing whitespace.
+   $env:PYTHONPATH = "$PWD/src"
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:16: trailing whitespace.
+   python -m prometheus_kernel serverforge install-url
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:17: trailing whitespace.
+   ```
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:18: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:19: trailing whitespace.
+5. Open the returned URL and approve installation into the preselected server.
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:20: trailing whitespace.
+6. Store the bot token in the current shell or a local secret manager—never in a repository file:
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:21: trailing whitespace.
+
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:22: trailing whitespace.
+   ```powershell
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:23: trailing whitespace.
+   $env:DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN = "YOUR_BOT_TOKEN"
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:24: trailing whitespace.
+   ```
docs/SERVERFORGE_BOOTSTRAP.md:25: trailing whitespace.
+
